default     Article 8(2) states:
default2   There shall be no interference by a public authority with the exercise of this right except such as is in accordance with the law and is necessary in a democratic society in the interests of national security [or] public safety . . . for the prevention of disorder or crime, . . . or for the protection of the rights and freedoms of others.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultArticle 8(1) Right to a private life
default&#xa0;default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default(a)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe physical and psychological integrity of a person and can therefore embrace multiple aspects of the person's physical and social identity.
default(b)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGender identification, name and sexual orientation and sexual life fall within the personal sphere protected by art.8. 
default(c)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBeyond a person’s name, his or her private and family life may include other means of personal identification and of linking to a family.
default(d)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default Information about the person’s health is an important element of private life.
default(e)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default An individual’s ethnic identity must be regarded as another such element. 
default(f)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
default A right to personal development, and the right to establish and develop relationships with other human beings and the outside world. 
default(g)
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe concept of private life includes elements relating to a person’s right to their image.
default&#xa0;
defaulti)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultthat it is in accordance with the law;
defaultii)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultthat it is carried out in pursuit of a legitimate aim; and
defaultiii)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultthat the interference is proportionate to the aim sought to be achieved.
defaultOnce a doctor’s case has concluded then the legitimate aim of protecting the public has been satisfied.
